                <a target="_blank" href="https://home.cern/" class="text-carrot hover:underline text-sm md:text-base">
                  CERN
                </a>
                <ul class="pt-4 space-y-1">
                  <li class="text-sm md:text-base text-neutral-700">EP-Dept./ISOLDE, 1211 Geneva 23, Switzerland</li>
                  <li class="text-sm md:text-base">+41 22 767 2783</li>
                  <li class="text-sm md:text-base "><a href="mailto:tim.enrico.lellinger@cern.ch" class="text-carrot hover:underline">tim.enrico.lellinger@cern.ch</a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>                                                   
            <p class="text-sm md:text-base mt-3">
              Edward Matthews contributes to the scientific endeavors of the COLLAPS experiment, working on areas such as data analysis, laser spectroscopy, or the development of experimental techniques and methodologies. His work would be part of broader efforts to explore and better understand the fundamental properties of matter at a nuclear level.          
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="bg-gray-100 p-8">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start md:items-center space-y-4 md:space-y-0 md:space-x-4">
              <div class="hidden md:flex-shrink-0 md:block w-32 h-40">
                <Image src={pfp} alt="Liss Vázquez Rodríguez" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
              </div>
              <div class="flex flex-col justify-center">
                <h3 class="text-black font-display text-xl md:text-2xl mb-2">Jack Hughes</h3>
                <a target="_blank" href="https://www.liverpool.ac.uk/" class="text-carrot hover:underline text-sm md:text-base">
                  Univesity of Liverpool
                </a>
                <ul class="pt-4 space-y-1">
                  <li class="text-sm md:text-base text-neutral-700">-</li>
                  <li class="text-sm md:text-base">-</li>
                  <li class="text-sm md:text-base "><a href="mailto:jbh@ns.ph.liv.ac.uk" class="text-carrot hover:underline">jbh@ns.ph.liv.ac.uk</a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>                                                   
            <p class="text-sm md:text-base mt-3">
              Jack Hughes is a physicist associated with the University of Liverpool. He is known for his work in the field of particle physics, particularly focusing on experimental high-energy physics. At the University of Liverpool, Hughes is involved in research that contributes to our understanding of the fundamental particles and forces that make up the universe.            </p>
